questions.explanation:
The given image shows a negatively skewed or a left-skewed distribution curve. Here, mean &lt; 
median &lt; mode. Mode is the most frequently occurring value in the distribution and is given by the highest point 
of the graph. Since the given graph has only one peak, it is unimodal. A positively skewed distribution refers to a right-skewed distribution. In such cases, mean &gt; 
median &gt; mode.
